A: The issue is that you are using the same iterator for all children in your loop. You should use the iterator of the current child in each loop iteration.
Here is the corrected code:
names=new ArrayList<>();
rootRef.addValueEventListener(new ValueEventListener() {
    @Override
    public void onDataChange(DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {
        for (DataSnapshot dataSnapshot1:dataSnapshot.getChildren()) {
            i = i + 1;
            Iterator<DataSnapshot> iterator = dataSnapshot1.getChildren().iterator();
            while (iterator.hasNext()) {
                names.add(iterator.next().getValue(String.class));
            }
        }
        Toast.makeText(signup.this,""+names,Toast.LENGTH_LONG).show();
    }

    @Override
    public void onCancelled(DatabaseError databaseError) {
        // Handle the error
    }
});

This code will iterate over all children of each child in the dataSnapshot and add their values to the names list.

